                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>P. <locus target="#1"/>: በስመ፡አብ፡"… ንቀድም፡በረድኤተ፡እግዚአብሔር፡ጸሒፈ፡መጽሐፈ፡ልፋፈ፡ጽድቅ፡ወጸሎተ፡ወመድኃኒት፡ዘጸሐፉ፡አብ፡በእደዊሁ፡ቅዱሳት።እምቅድመ፡ይትፈጠሩ፡ሰማያት፡ወምድር፡ወእምቅድመ፡ይትፈጠሩ፡መላእክት፡ወሰብእ፨</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>The manuscript is an “accordion book” (sǝnsul) composed of four folded parchment strips sewn together (pp. <locus target="#0"/>-<locus target="#11"/>
                              <locus from="12" to="23"/>, <locus from="23" to="31"/>, <locus from="32" to="33"/>/<locus target="#34"/>; the length is <locus target="#73"/>.<locus target="#4 #75"/>.<locus target="#2 #49"/>.<locus target="#4 #10"/>.<locus target="#8"/>cm, resp.). Three are sewn together with purple threads and the forth with white threads.</p>
                           <p>The incipit page is protected by a small folded leaf (p. <locus target="#0"/>). The only wooden (back) board is attached on one pair of sewing stations to the fold of pp. <locus from="32" to="33"/>/<locus target="#34"/>.</p>
                           
                        </decoNote>
                     </binding>
